Package: mono-tools
Version: 1.2.1
Revision: 1021
Description: Tools for use with the Mono runtime
License: GPL
Maintainer: Benjamin Reed <mono-tools@fink.racoonfink.com>

Depends: gecko-sharp (>= 2.0-1029), gtk-sharp2 (>= 2.4.2-1022), mono (>= 1.1.18-1), monodoc (>= 1.1.13-1022)
BuildDepends: fink (>= 0.24-1), gconf2-dev (>= 2.20.0-1), gecko-sharp (>= 2.0-1029), gtk-sharp2 (>= 2.4.2-1022), libglade2 (>= 2.6.2-1), mono-dev (>= 1.1.14-1021), monodoc (>= 1.1.13-1022)

Source: http://go-mono.com/sources/%n/%n-%v.tar.gz
Source-MD5: d65587a842799f2e087ef101bcb4c68a

ConfigureParams: --mandir=%p/share/man --disable-dependency-tracking PKG_CONFIG_PATH="%p/lib/pango-ft219/lib/pkgconfig:%p/lib/fontconfig2/lib/pkgconfig:%p/lib/freetype219/lib/pkgconfig:$PKG_CONFIG_PATH" PATH="%p/lib/freetype219/bin:$PATH" FREETYPE_CONFIG=%p/lib/freetype219/bin/freetype-config
CompileScript: <<
#!/bin/sh -ex

	export lt_cv_sys_max_cmd_len=65536
	export MONO_PATH=%b/browser:$MONO_PATH
	./configure %c
	make
<<

InstallScript: <<
#!/bin/sh -ex

	export MONO_PATH="%i/lib:$MONO_PATH"
	make install DESTDIR="%d" mkinstalldirs='$(install_sh) -d'
<<

PreInstScript: <<
	if [ -f "%p/var/lib/dpkg/info/monodoc.postrm" ] && [ `grep -c upgrade "%p/var/lib/dpkg/info/monodoc.postrm"` = 0 ]; then
	  sudo echo "#!/bin/sh" > "%p/var/lib/dpkg/info/monodoc.postrm"
	  sudo echo "exit 0" >> "%p/var/lib/dpkg/info/monodoc.postrm"
	fi
<<
PostInstScript: 	[ -x "%p/bin/monodoc" ] && [ -d "%p/lib/monodoc" ] && "%p/bin/monodoc" --make-index >/dev/null 2>&1 || :
PostRmScript: <<
	if [ "upgrade" != "$1" ]; then
	  rm -rf %p/lib/monodoc
	fi
<<

Homepage: http://www.go-mono.org/
DescDetail: <<
A collection of tools and utilities for use with the
Mono runtime environment.
<<

